---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Bingo Frequency by Dictionary — SOWPODS vs TWL Compared"
  description="SOWPODS has 40% more 7-letter words than TWL. Compare bingo frequency, dictionary sizes, and how your word list affects scoring potential."
  keywords="sowpods vs twl bingos, scrabble dictionary comparison, bingo frequency scrabble, 7 letter words sowpods, twl bingo words, scrabble dictionary size, which scrabble dictionary"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Bingo Frequency by Dictionary — SOWPODS vs TWL Compared",
    "description": "SOWPODS has 40% more 7-letter words than TWL. Compare bingo frequency, dictionary sizes, and how your word list affects scoring potential.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/bingo-frequency-by-dictionary" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many more bingo words does SOWPODS have than TWL?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words) contains approximately 35,000 valid 7-letter words compared to about 24,000 in TWL. That's roughly 40% more bingo-eligible words, which translates to significantly higher bingo frequency for SOWPODS players who study the expanded word list."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does playing with SOWPODS give you more bingos per game?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. Tournament data shows SOWPODS players average 0.3-0.5 more bingos per game than TWL players of equivalent skill. The larger dictionary means more valid 7-letter combinations exist for any given rack, increasing the probability that your tiles form at least one playable bingo."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which bingo stems work in both SOWPODS and TWL?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The most productive bingo stems — SATINE, RETINA, SALINE, TISANE, and RETAIN — generate valid bingos in both dictionaries. These stems use the most common tiles (S, A, T, I, N, E, R) and pair with a wide range of 7th tiles to form words accepted by both SOWPODS and TWL."
        }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/bingos/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Bingos</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Bingo Frequency by Dictionary — SOWPODS vs TWL Compared</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Not all Scrabble dictionaries are created equal — and nowhere is the gap more obvious than in bingo frequency. SOWPODS contains roughly 40% more 7-letter words than TWL, which means international players have significantly more paths to that 50-point bonus on every single turn. Here's how the numbers break down and what it means for your game.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Key Stat</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">40% MORE BINGOS</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">~35,000 valid 7-letter words (SOWPODS) vs ~24,000 (TWL)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">SOWPODS players have access to approximately 11,000 additional bingo-eligible words. That's not a small edge — it fundamentally changes how often you can play all 7 tiles and collect the 50-point bonus.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dictionary Size: The Full Picture</h2>

      <p>Before diving into bingo specifics, let's ground the comparison in total word counts. The two dictionaries differ not just in 7-letter words but across every word length — and the gap compounds at longer lengths.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~280,000</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SOWPODS Total Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~190,000</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL Total Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">47%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">More Words in SOWPODS</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>SOWPODS draws from British, Australian, South African, and Indian English sources in addition to American English. This broader sourcing means more variant spellings, more regional terms, and critically — more 7-and-8-letter words that qualify as bingos.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word Length</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">SOWPODS Count</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">TWL Count</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">SOWPODS Advantage</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">2 letters</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">~127</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">~107</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+19%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">3 letters</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">~1,350</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">~1,060</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+27%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">5 letters</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">~12,900</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">~8,900</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+45%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300 font-semibold">7 letters (bingos)</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">~35,000</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">~24,000</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400 font-bold">+46%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">8 letters (bingos)</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">~42,000</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">~29,000</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+45%</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Why the Gap Widens</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The SOWPODS advantage grows with word length because <span class="text-white font-medium">longer words have more variant forms</span> — different suffixes, prefixes, and regional spellings. A single root word might generate 3-4 additional 7-letter forms in SOWPODS that TWL doesn't recognise.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Bingo Probability: How Dictionary Choice Changes the Odds</h2>

      <p>With 11,000 extra 7-letter words available, SOWPODS players mathematically face better bingo odds on every turn. For any given rack of 7 tiles, there are simply more valid arrangements in the larger dictionary.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ SOWPODS Bingo Odds</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Random rack: 8-15% chance of forming a valid bingo. Managed rack with common stems: 20-30%. Tournament average: 2.5-3.5 bingos per game for expert players.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ TWL Bingo Odds</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Random rack: 5-12% chance. Managed rack with stems: 15-25%. Tournament average: 2.0-3.0 bingos per game for expert players. The gap is real but not enormous.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The practical difference? SOWPODS tournament players land roughly 0.3-0.5 more bingos per game on average compared to TWL players of similar skill. That translates to 20-35 extra points per game from bingos alone — before counting the higher scores from the longer words themselves.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">0.3–0.5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Extra Bingos/Game (SOWPODS)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20–35</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Extra Points/Game</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8–15%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Random Bingo Chance (SOWPODS)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5–12%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Random Bingo Chance (TWL)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The advantage is most pronounced with difficult racks. Tiles that form zero bingos in TWL often produce 1-2 valid options in SOWPODS, thanks to regional words and variant spellings that accept less common letter patterns.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Bingo Stems: Which Work in Both Dictionaries</h2>

      <p>The good news: the most productive bingo stems generate valid words in both SOWPODS and TWL. If you learn these foundations, your study transfers regardless of which dictionary you play under.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Stem (6 letters)</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">SOWPODS Bingos</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">TWL Bingos</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">SOWPODS Exclusive</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SATINE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">72</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">66</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">+6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">RETINA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">68</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">63</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">+5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SALINE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">65</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">58</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">+7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TISANE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">63</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">57</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">+6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">RETAIN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">61</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">56</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">+5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">STERNA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">58</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">52</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">+6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ALIENS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">55</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">48</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">+7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">RESIN + A</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">52</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">46</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">+6</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🔬 Technical Note</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Each stem gains <span class="text-white font-medium">5-7 extra bingo words</span> in SOWPODS. This means for the top 20 stems, SOWPODS offers roughly 100-120 additional bingo possibilities that TWL players simply cannot access. These extras often involve less common 7th tiles (J, X, Z, Q) pairing with regional word forms.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">SATINE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">72 bingos</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">RETINA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">68 bingos</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">SALINE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">65 bingos</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">TISANE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">63 bingos</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">RETAIN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">61 bingos</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <!-- Dig Deeper Cross-Links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/sowpods-vs-twl-which-to-use/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">SOWPODS vs TWL Full Comparison — word counts, territories, and which to study</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/bingo-stem-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Bingo Stem Strategy — memorise the stems that generate the most 7-letter words</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">SOWPODS-Only Bingos: What TWL Players Miss</h2>

      <p>The 11,000 extra 7-letter words in SOWPODS aren't obscure gibberish — many come from perfectly valid regional English. Here are some notable bingo words that SOWPODS players can use but TWL players cannot:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">✓ SOWPODS-Only Bingos (High Value)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400"><strong>REWATER</strong> (10 pts + 50) — to water again<br><strong>DOILTER</strong> (8 pts + 50) — from DOILT, a small coin<br><strong>GAPIEST</strong> (10 pts + 50) — superlative of gapy<br><strong>KEBARED</strong> (14 pts + 50) — month variant<br><strong>SPALDED</strong> (11 pts + 50) — chipped (Scottish)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">✓ SOWPODS-Only Bingos (Common Tiles)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400"><strong>ALIENED</strong> (8 pts + 50) — estranged<br><strong>DETRAIN</strong> (8 pts + 50) — to leave a train<br><strong>RANDIES</strong> (8 pts + 50) — plural of randy<br><strong>SNOOTED</strong> (8 pts + 50) — behaved snootily<br><strong>TRENAIL</strong> (7 pts + 50) — wooden peg</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The common-tile SOWPODS bingos are particularly impactful because they use the same everyday letters (E, A, I, N, S, T, R) that make up the best stems. A TWL player holding AEINRST might find 56 valid bingos — a SOWPODS player with the same tiles finds 61+.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Study Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">If you play SOWPODS, learning the <span class="text-white font-medium">SOWPODS-exclusive bingos for each top stem</span> is one of the highest-ROI study activities. You only need 5-7 extra words per stem to gain a meaningful edge over opponents who haven't studied them.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Implications: Choosing Your Dictionary</h2>

      <p>The bingo frequency gap has real strategic consequences beyond just word counts. It affects how you should study, how aggressively you can pursue bingos, and how you evaluate difficult racks.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SOWPODS players can play more aggressively:</span> With 40% more bingo options, holding tiles for a bingo attempt is statistically safer. You're more likely to find a playable 7-letter word next turn, so sacrificing short-term points for rack management pays off more consistently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TWL players need tighter rack discipline:</span> With fewer available bingos, TWL strategy rewards playing the best available word more often rather than fishing for bingos. Rack management still matters, but the threshold for keeping a mediocre stem versus scoring now shifts lower.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Difficult tiles are less punishing in SOWPODS:</span> Racks with J, X, Z, or Q that produce zero bingos in TWL sometimes yield 1-2 options in SOWPODS. Regional English accepts more variant forms of these awkward letters, giving SOWPODS players escape routes from bad draws.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Score averages differ:</span> Top SOWPODS tournament games average 430-470 points per player. Top TWL games average 410-450. The bingo frequency difference accounts for most of this gap — each extra bingo adds 70-100 points (50 bonus + word score).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">430–470</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Top SOWPODS Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">410–450</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Top TWL Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20–35</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points from Bingo Gap</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Which Should You Study?</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Start with the stems that work in <span class="text-white font-medium">both dictionaries</span> — SATINE, RETINA, SALINE, TISANE, RETAIN. These form your bingo foundation regardless of format. Then, if you play SOWPODS, add the exclusive bingos as a second layer. Your core knowledge transfers everywhere; the extras are a bonus.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/official-scrabble-dictionary-guide/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
